### POST `/zalo-accounts/make-friend`
#### Endpoint
- Method: `POST`
- Full path: `/zalo-accounts/make-friend`
- Function: `ZaloAccountsController.createFriend`

#### Description
Create a friend relationship between two Zalo accounts using the `ZaloAccountFriend` model. A newly created relationship always starts with status `PENDING`. If a matching relationship already exists with status `CANCEL`, the backend reuses that record and changes its status back to `PENDING` instead of creating a duplicate row.

#### Request
- Params: none
- Query: none
- Body:
  - `masterId`: `string`, required, UUID of the source account
  - `friendId`: `string`, required, UUID of the friend account

Example request:

```json
{
  "masterId": "7c13f32f-90eb-483f-b5e0-c3b7fa120001",
  "friendId": "7c13f32f-90eb-483f-b5e0-c3b7fa120002"
}
```

#### Response

```json
{
  "id": "4df1ab59-8f3c-4c28-9b36-8b0c95de0010",
  "createdAt": "2026-04-16T08:45:00.000Z",
  "status": "PENDING",
  "master": {
    "id": "7c13f32f-90eb-483f-b5e0-c3b7fa120001",
    "zaloId": "0987654321",
    "phone": "0901234567",
    "name": "Master Account",
    "isMaster": true
  },
  "friend": {
    "id": "7c13f32f-90eb-483f-b5e0-c3b7fa120002",
    "zaloId": "1122334455",
    "phone": "0909999999",
    "name": "Child Account",
    "isMaster": false
  }
}
```

#### Error cases
- `400`: validation error or both IDs are the same
- `401`: missing/invalid JWT
- `403`: role is not allowed
- `404`: one of the Zalo accounts was not found
- `409`: friend relationship already exists in either direction with status other than `CANCEL`
- `500`: unexpected server error

#### Authentication
- JWT required
- Guards: `JwtAuthGuard`, `RolesGuard`
- Roles: authenticated `ADMIN` or `USER`

